    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Peirce</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 69.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received Mr. Breckinridge’s No. 71,
                            of the 17th ultimo, inclosing copy of his note to the Russian foreign
                            office in regard to the refusal of the Russian consul-general at New
                            York to visé passports for American citizens of Jewish faith.</p>
                <p>His note is approved.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
